{"id":460411425,"lang":"cpp","lang_name":"C++","time":"1 year, 10 months","timestamp":1614231863,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"40 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/460411425/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum IV - Input is a BST","memory":"38 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * struct TreeNode {\n *     int val;\n *     TreeNode *left;\n *     TreeNode *right;\n *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}\n * };\n */\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    bool findTarget(TreeNode* root, int k) {\n        std::set<int> s;\n        std::queue<TreeNode *> q;\n        q.push(root);\n        while (!q.empty())\n        {\n            auto n = q.front();\n            q.pop();\n            if (s.find(k - n->val) != s.end())\n                return true;\n            s.insert(n->val);\n            if (n->left != nullptr)\n            {\n                q.push(n->left);\n            }\n            if (n->right != nullptr)\n            {\n                q.push(n->right);\n            }\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"two-sum-iv-input-is-a-bst","has_notes":false,"notes":"","topic_tags":[]}
